Getting Started

    TrueVFS is a multi-module project which is built by
    {{{http://maven.apache.org}Apache Maven}}, so all its artifacts are hosted
    on
    {{{http://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Cg%3A%22net.java.truevfs%22%20AND%20v%3A%22${project.version}%22}Maven Central}}.
    You can start a TrueVFS application project
    {{{./maven.html}with}}
    or
    {{{./no-maven.html}without}}
    Maven by following the respective guide in the menu on the left of this
    page.
    Once you've setup your project, you should read the short
    {{{./tutorial.html}TrueVFS Tutorial}} to learn about the client APIs.

    If you use Maven, the
    {{{../truevfs-archetype/truevfs-archetype-access/index.html}TrueVFS&#160;Archetype&#160;Access}}
    provides lots of sample code.
    In addition, there is more sample code and applications available in the
    {{{../truevfs-samples/index.html}TrueVFS&#160;Samples}} module.
    Please
    {{{../truevfs-samples/source-repository.html}check out}} or
    {{{http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/net/java/truevfs/truevfs-samples/${project.version}/truevfs-samples-${project.version}-sources.jar}download}}
    its source code.
